response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: Sum of Squares\", \"description\": \"Given a list of integers, calculate the sum of the squares of all odd numbers in the list. \\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef sum_of_squares_odd(nums: list[int]) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `nums` (list[int]): A list of integers.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the sum of the squares of all odd numbers in the input list.\\n\", \"code\": \"def sum_of_squares_odd(nums: list[int]) -> int:\\n    return sum(num ** 2 for num in nums if num % 2 != 0)\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert sum_of_squares_odd([1, 2, 3, 4, 5]) == 25\", \"assert sum_of_squares_odd([-1, -3, 1, 3]) == 14\", \"assert sum_of_squares_odd([2, 4, 6, 8]) == 0\", \"assert sum_of_squares_odd([]) == 0\"] }"
